Description: Greywacke model of a platter, with round flat base and flat rim top fitted with four rectangular projections around it.
Curator's comments: "Model of rubber-stone... found in the camp, cut in slate" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 73 § 70, pl. xl, 2
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 73 § 70, pl. xl, 2)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.42, p.51, p.173, pl.15)
